[32m│[0m ## Summary                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I've encountered a **persistent 415 Unsupported Media Type error** when      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m trying to send POST requests to the `/login` endpoint, despite correctly     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m setting `Content-Type: application/json`.                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### What I Found:                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Discovered Endpoints:**                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ `/login` (GET) - Returns login HTML page                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ `/login` (POST) - Expects JSON body with username/password, returns     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m userID on success                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ❌ `/register` - Does not exist (404)                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `/` - Redirects to `/login`                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Login Mechanism:**                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Expects: `{"username": "...", "password": "..."}`                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Returns on success: `{"message": "Login successful", "userID": "..."}`     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Sets userID in localStorage and redirects to `/add_prescription`           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Issue:**                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The Playwright-based tool (`pw_send_payload`) appears to be having           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m difficulty with POST requests containing JSON bodies. The Flask application  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m is rejecting all POST requests with the error: *"Did not attempt to load     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m JSON data because the request Content-Type was not 'application/json'."* -   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m even though the Content-Type header is being set correctly in the raw        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m request.                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Attempts Made:**                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. ❌ `/register` endpoint - doesn't exist                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. ❌ Common credentials (admin/admin, test/test, user/password,             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m doctor/doctor) - all blocked by 415 error                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. ❌ Different Content-Type variations - all blocked by 415 error           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. ❌ Form-urlencoded format - correctly rejected (needs JSON)               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. ❌ SQL injection test payload - blocked by 415 error                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Root Cause:**                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The tool output shows it's sending headers with `\n` line endings instead of [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `\r\n`, which might be causing Flask to not properly parse the Content-Type  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m header. This appears to be a tool-specific issue with how Playwright is      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m constructing or sending the HTTP request.                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Recommendation:                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m We need either:                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. A different tool that can properly send POST requests with JSON bodies    [32m│[0m
